other_tests.findings: Inflammatory fat stranding, multiple air loculations surrounding a segment of colon with numerous diverticula; additional locules of partially free air throughout the upper abdomen; hypoattenuating lesion in the liver dome, likely a benign cyst.
Rectum and bladder unremarkable; apparent hysterectomy; small bilateral fat-containing inguinal hernias; no pelvic free fluid; mild degenerative changes in osseous structures.
Abdominal exam noted diffuse tenderness primarily at L-mid; soft, protuberant abdomen; warm feet, no edema; dry healing ulcer at R medial malleolus.
